Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: salary-timetracker-sqlite
Version: 0.2
Summary: A simple and easy timetracker for loging working hours with sqlite db and automatic wage calculation.
Home-page: http://github.com/dalay/salary-timetracker-sqlite
Author: Alexandr Jurow
Author-email: pythonwayru@gmail.com
License: GPL
Download-URL: https://github.com/dalay/salary-timetracker-sqlite/archive/v0.2.tar.gz
Description: A handy tool with a command line interface for logging time worked. At
        any time you can see how much you have spent time on a particular
        project and how much you have earned on it.
        
        Installation
        ------------
        
        .. code:: bash
        
           pip install salary-timetracker-sqlite
        
        Usage
        -----
        
        .. code:: bash
        
           tts [OPTIONS]
        
           To add a new entry just enter 'tts'. If there are no options, an interactive session is started.
        
           Options:
             -a, --show-all     Show all entries
             -p, --show-paid    Show paid
             -u, --show-unpaid  Show unpaid
             -s, --stats        Show unpaid hours
             -m, --mark-paid    Mark all hours worked as paid
             --del-paid         Delete records marked as paid
             --help             Show this message and exit.
        
